                <td width="55" height="21" align="center">8</td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td align="left" style="padding:5 10" width="388"><font class="title01">Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc. Reports Increase in Operating Profits, Marginal Fall in Sales</font> </td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td width="100" align="center">Apr.20,2005</td>
              </tr>
			  <tr class="bbs05"> 
                <td height="1" colspan="5"><img src="/english/images/blank.gif"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bbs03"> 
                <td colspan="2" height="21" align="center">&nbsp;</td>
                <td colspan="3" align="left" style="padding:5 10">SEOUL, April 20, 2005 - Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc. (Pantech&Curitel, KRX: 063350), one of the world’s leading mobile communications companies, today announced unaudited earnings results for the three-month period ended March 31, 2005.<br>
<br>
Sales for the first quarter of 2005 fell 2.2% to KRW520.3 billion, compared to the fourth quarter of 2004, but operating profits for the same period rose by 242% to KRW16.6 billion. Domestic sales rose by 68% in the first quarter of 2005, compared to the fourth quarter of 2004, to KRW216.7 billion with shipments up by 90% to a total 0.73 million units. <br>
<br>
Demand for handsets in the domestic Korean market went up by 52%, largely based on the introduction of full-scale Mobile Net Portability (MNP), where handset owners can keep their cell phone numbers, regardless of their choice of carriers. <br>
<br>
Dr. Moon S. Song, President & CEO of Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc., said: “The dramatic jump in operating profits can be largely attributed to strong growth in domestic sales, as well as an increase in average unit sales price. Although cyclicality is always a factor, we believe our latest results show that we have significantly strengthened our position in the domestic Korean market.” <br>
<br>
Overseas sales during the first quarter of 2005 dropped by 24.6% to KRW303.5 billion, compared to the fourth quarter of 2004, with overseas shipments falling by 22.6% to a total of 1.94 million units.<br>
<br>
“Taking variations in seasonal demand into account, we are satisfied with the level of our overseas sales over the last quarter. The fact of the matter is that our average quarterly shipment throughout the whole of 2004 was 1.8 million units, so the shipment for the first quarter of 2005 actually shows that we are improving steadily overall,” said Dr. Song.<br>
<br>
“We are confident that we will be able to maintain these positive trends over the coming year, with strong product lines in Korea and across our global markets, supported by aggressive marketing and branding strategies,” he said.<br>
</td>
              </tr>
